texts.text: *Howl*
I have you now! Prepare yourself!
Rika, get back!
*Screech*
>A hidden demon attacks and narrowly misses Rika.
Thank you, Megakin!
Don't get too close! It's game over if you're surrounded.
I understand, but we must reduce their numbers soon or...
Keh-keh-keh. Look! Humans!
They're pretty feisty. Seems like we're in for a treat.
Tryin' to beat us in numbers, eh?
Then we'll cut straight past 'em!
Understood!
We won, but the situation is dire.
Agreed. We've defeated so many but there's no end in sight.
It's clear they'll eventually overwhelm us.
It sucks, but we gotta beat their kingpin like that Divine said.
Like, it REALLY sucks.
That's our Shionyan! Always rational for the sake of the mission!
*Scoff* What do you take me for? Can't you see I'm pissed as it is?
As punishment, slice open your pork belly and apologize. Now.
As you wish!
But I have a posthumous request! Please behead me afterward!
Denied. Shiang can finish you off.
Um, why me?
Because I don't want dirty pig blood on me.
And you think I do...?
At any rate, let's think of a way to defeat this boss.
Insufficient data will limit our options, but...
Nah, there's gotta somethin'.
How's it lookin', Kokoro? Any luck?
Yup! Thanks for waiting!
I looked into Rahab and the other world and struck gold!

"The other world"...
Of course!
Like we thought.
That angel said Rahab sent demons from an alternate world.
We've dealt with this stuff before.
You mean Gozu-Tennoh, right?
Yes, that was also due to anomalies in the Dragon Stream.
The power of another world disrupted its flow.
It's the same pattern this time, only a different dimension.
The Dragon Stream can't seem to catch a break.
And that's why our world is so unstable?
One problem at a time.
So, were you able to pinpoint this Rahab guy's home world?
Yes! It was easy-peasy once I confirmed the space distortion!
But like before, I can only send a select few.
I did my best to hang in there last time, but two is my limit.
That's all you'll have against Rahab.
A skeleton crew, eh?
It can't be helped. Besides, there's enough demon trouble here.
The rest of us will focus on dealing with them.
Good point. The question is, who's it gonna be?
Um, might I volunteer?
Rika? Why so eager?
Before we met up, I saw people being attacked by demons.
They were normal citizens with no means to defend themselves.
I wish to put an end to this as soon as possible.
So, you wanna protect others. Nice! I like your spunk!
Well, that's one down. Now, who else...
I'll join her.
I'll go.
I'll go.
Oh, Newbie! We've got a volunteer!
Thank you. I'll be glad to have someone with travel experience.
Still, this time it's a totally different world.
Anyways, it looks like we're all set! Let's dive right in!
We're countin' on you two. Go and whoop Rahab's ass!
Of course. We'll report back later.
>[sys user_name] and Rika head to the alternate world.
>They feel an odd weightlessness.
>Then, led only by Kokoro's voice, the pair move forward.
>Finally, their eyes open, and...
We're heeere! Thank you for your patience!
*Gulp* So, we've finally arrived.
So this an alternate world...
It looks different.
That's right.
Of course it does. There are countless other dimensions.
Even Newbie hasn't been to this one before.
In fact, it's a big moment for you as a multiverse traveler!
It feels quite different from our world.
Nah, that's just the atmosphere. Everything else is pretty similar.
Out of countless universes, you really lucked out with this one!
I see.
I'm certainly curious about what awaits us,
but Rahab is our top priority.
Let's go.
Hmm. This scenery goes on forever.
Yes. And we've hardly seen any sign of life, let alone humans.
I had expected a horde of demons to ambush us...
But perhaps they're hiding or are already off to our own world.
But I guess now we can avoid pointless battles, right?
A Super Priestess like me is the luckiest charm you'll ever find!
You mean fortune favors us? Let's hope so.
We can handle any situation if we keep up our strength.
Exactly! When things look tough, you've gotta think positive!
All-righty! Let's stay strong and find Rahab!
You called, woman?
Huh?! No way...!
...There he is.
Rahab!
*Chuckle* I haven't conversed with a human in ages.
State your business with me, mortals.
